iron.iron.core

These are the main domain classes. They represent the things the system is built around.

User

Represents a general system user. This can act as a parent class for all user types so that shared fields like ID and name do not have to be repeated.

Organizer

Represents an organizer who can create and manage races. This class is responsible for organizer-specific behavior such as setting race details or submitting results.

Racer

Represents a racer in the system. This class stores racer information like category, payment information, license, and race history, and supports actions like registering for races or reviewing them.

Admin

Represents an administrator who oversees the system. This class handles administrative responsibilities such as managing users, licenses, and system settings.

Race

Represents a race event. This class stores important race details such as title, date, type, distance, route, participant limit, registration deadline, and whether the race is official or unofficial.

Stage

Represents a stage within a race. This is useful if a race contains multiple parts or sections, each with its own distance or route information.

License

Represents a racer’s racing license. This class stores the license ID, issue date, expiration date, category level, and whether the license is active.

RaceRegistration

Represents a racer’s registration for a specific race. This class connects a racer to a race and tracks information like registration date and status.

RaceResults

Represents the results of a racer in a race. This class stores race outcome data such as placement and whether the racer earned a podium finish.

RaceReview

Represents a review left by a racer after a race. This class stores a rating and comment connected to both the racer and the race.

Notification

Represents a notification sent to a racer. This can be used for messages such as registration confirmation, race reminders, or category upgrade alerts.